			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You are correct, the past history doesn't effect the chance of the next "toss." 
<br />

<br />
Using the coin-toss analogy, you are looking at the chances that you will get, for example, at least two heads in a given number of future tosses. You chances of getting two heads out of two tosses is pretty low. You have a somewhat better chance at getting two (or even three) heads out of three tosses. The more times you plan on flipping the coin, the higher your chances are of getting two or more.
<br />

<br />
The chances of getting the drop on the nth kill don't change. The chances that you will see it, for example, at least twice increase the more times you plan on killing the mob.
<br />

<br />
Whether you have killed the mob one or 20 times, you still need to start at the top of the table for the next kill. The past is fixed; the table gives a glimpse into the chances for the <span style="font-style: italic">next </span>kills.
<br />

<br />
The table answers the question, "Given that I don't have the piece yet, how long am I likely to have to wait to see it <span style="font-style: italic">from today?" </span>With time, others may get the piece ahead of you, you need fewer drops until you get "yours," so your "expected wait time" will be less when you stare into its fangs.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=568700" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Itchyban of Veeshan</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td class="row1" width="150" align="left" valign="middle"><span class="nav"><a href="#top" class="nav">Back to top</a></span></td>
