			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I ran through that similar math once when I was working on the Iksar SK progressive quest weapon.  There is a mob that you camp that drops 7 lore pages.  I can't remember if it drops it every time, but for the sake of discussion, let's say it drops it 100% of the time.  That seems like a decent chance of getting the drop, right?  If your 100% lucky, you only need to kill the mob 7 times.
<br />

<br />
To bad life doesn't work that way <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
You get the first drop, that leaves you with a 6/7 chance that you will get a new page on the next kill.  And it get's progressively worse.  Let's say that you figure that you would have to kill on average 1.167 (that is 1 / 6/7) mobs (I know, how do you get a fraction of a mob) to get that second page.  Add up those fractional mobs for each progressive page.  So the third page you would have to kill 1.4 mobs (1 / 5/7), etc. etc...
<br />

<br />
That gives you a total of 1 + 1.167 + 1.4 + 1.75 + 2.333 + 3.5 + 7 = 17.15 mobs on average that you are going to have to kill to get all those pages.  Doesn't seem to be that easy of a task now...
<br />

<br />
Let's say the mob drops a page only 20% of the time.  That will increase 5-fold on average the number of mobs that you will have to kill, so 85.75 mobs.
<br />

<br />
What makes it worse is that it gets progressively more difficult to get that final page.  In the 100% scenario, you will have to kill an average of 7 mobs to get that final page.  In a 20% scenario, you will need to kill 35 mobs to get that final page.  Even if the mob is on a 5 minute spawn cycle (without PHs), you will be camping it for almost 3 hours for that last page.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://scrubfire.dyndns.org/KJ_Sig.jpg" border="0" />
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=121470" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold">Kennethjames Scrubfire, Arch Convoker</span></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
